# ==============================================================================
# Hermes Agent — DeepSeek Configuration Template
# ==============================================================================
# Copy this file to ~/.hermes/.env (or source from Hermes config.yaml).
# Never commit real API keys. Replace *** with production/development values.
# ==============================================================================
#
# This project (gaijinn-memory-fs / Obsidian vault civilization) uses:
#   Provider: DeepSeek (deepseek-v4-flash)
#   Orchestrator mode: Hermes -> grid workers (16x DeepSeek subagents)
#   Executor profile: deepseek (configured in .gaijinn/project.json)
#
# Full setup guide: 20_Projects/deepseek-hermes-setup.md
#
# Worker-002 atomic sprint provenance (2026-06-19, WU-006, grid-spawn-1196463):
#   This template is the canonical reference for the deepseek-grid executor
#   (see project.executor-profile.json > profiles.deepseek-grid). Worker-002
#   operates in MiniMax-M3 orchestrator + deepseek-v4-flash grid mode and
#   never embeds real API keys — only the *** placeholder pattern.
# ==============================================================================

# ==============================================================================
# DEEPSEEK PROVIDER
# ==============================================================================
# Primary API key — create at https://platform.deepseek.com/api_keys
# Keep this in ~/.hermes/.env, never in version control.
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=***

# Optional: Custom base URL (default: https://api.deepseek.com/v1)
# Use for proxy/gateway setups (e.g., local CCX bridge, Cloudflare workers)
# DEEPSEEK_BASE_URL=https://api.deepseek.com/v1

# Optional: Override model (default: deepseek-v4-flash)
# DEEPSEEK_MODEL=deepseek-v4-flash

# ==============================================================================
# CONFIG PRECEDENCE (overlay order, highest wins)
# ==============================================================================
# When the same parameter is set in multiple places, Gaijinn resolves in this
# priority order (1 = highest priority):
#
# | Rank | Source | Scope | Notes |
# |------|--------|-------|-------|
# | 1 | CLI flag (--model, --provider) | Per-invocation | Session-scoped override |
# | 2 | Export env var (export DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=...) | Shell session | Not persisted across terminals |
# | 3 | ~/.hermes/.env (this file) | User global | Grid workers read from here |
# | 4 | ~/.hermes/config.yaml (hermes login) | User global | CLI interactive login stores here |
# | 5 | .gaijinn/project.json (executor_profile) | Per-project | Defaults if nothing higher set |
# | 6 | Gaijinn default | Binary default | deepseek / deepseek-v4-flash |
#
# Grid worker spawns resolve auth from rank 3 (.env file). Rank 4 (config.yaml)
# credentials from `hermes login` do NOT propagate to workers.
#
# ==============================================================================
# DUAL AUTH — FAILOVER CHAIN
# ==============================================================================
# Hermes tries these auth methods in order (first to succeed wins):
#
# | Order | Method | Who Uses It | Key Variables |
# |-------|--------|-------------|---------------|
# | 1st   | API key (env file) | Grid workers, orchestrator | DEEPSEEK_API_KEY |
# | 2nd   | OAuth refresh token | Automated rotation | DEEPSEEK_REFRESH_TOKEN, CLIENT_ID, CLIENT_SECRET |
# | 3rd   | CLI interactive login | Human-orchestrator sessions | ~/.hermes/config.yaml (hermes login) |
#
# Option 1: DEEPSEEK_API_KEY in env file (above — highest priority runtime)
#   Simplest. Used by BOTH orchestrator and grid worker spawns.
#   Set DEEPSEEK_API_KEY in ~/.hermes/.env. Workers inherit automatically.
#
# Option 2: OAuth refresh token flow
#   Used when API key rotation is automated or CI/CD pipelines.
#   Obtain from DeepSeek platform → API Keys → OAuth App.
# DEEPSEEK_REFRESH_TOKEN=***
# DEEPSEEK_CLIENT_ID=***
# DEEPSEEK_CLIENT_SECRET=***
#
# Option 3: Hermes CLI interactive login
#   Run: hermes login && hermes model
#   Select: provider=deepseek, model=deepseek-v4-flash
#   Credentials stored in ~/.hermes/config.yaml.
#   CAUTION: CLI credentials are NOT inherited by grid worker spawns.
#            Workers require DEEPSEEK_API_KEY in the env file (Option 1).
#
# API Key Rotation:
#   When rotating DEEPSEEK_API_KEY, update all locations:
#   1. ~/.hermes/.env (primary key — grid workers read from here)
#   2. ~/.hermes/config.yaml if using hermes login (re-run hermes login)
#   3. .gaijinn/project.json if deepseek_provider contains embedded keys
#   Grid workers pick up the new key from .env immediately — no restart needed.
#
# GPG-Signed Commit Workflow (Gaijinn convention):
#   This repository signs all git commits with GPG key 432F5C1590D959EC.
#   When rotating credentials, ensure git config is also updated:
#     git config user.signingkey 432F5C1590D959EC
#     git config commit.gpgsign true
#   The env template itself is never committed with real keys — always replace
#   *** with production values in ~/.hermes/.env only.

# ==============================================================================
# ORCHESTRATOR (Hermes itself — connects to API for orchestration)
# ==============================================================================
# HERMES_DEFAULT_MODEL=deepseek-v4-flash
# HERMES_DEFAULT_PROVIDER=deepseek

# ==============================================================================
# GRID WORKER EXECUTION (subagent provisioning)
# ==============================================================================
# GRID_WORKER_MODEL=deepseek-v4-flash
# GRID_WORKER_PROVIDER=deepseek
# GRID_WORKER_TIMEOUT=300

# ==============================================================================
# VOICE TERMINAL (on-device speech i/o)
# ==============================================================================
# VOICE_ENABLED=true
# VOICE_PROVIDER=edge
# VOICE_INPUT_DEVICE=alsa_input.usb-MV-SILICON
# HERMES_SAY_COMMAND=hermes-say
# HERMES_TALK_COMMAND=hermes-talk

# ==============================================================================
# FILESYSTEM & WORKER INFRASTRUCTURE
# ==============================================================================
PROJECT_ROOT=/home/ghost-monday/Desktop/Gaijinn/vaults/gaijinn-memory-fs
# GAUGE_BLUEPRINT_PATH=.gaijinn/blueprint.json
# GAUGE_WORKERS_PATH=.gaijinn/workers

# ==============================================================================
# CRON & GATEWAY — UNATTENDED PIPELINE EXECUTION
# ==============================================================================
# Enable the gateway for the hermes-development-loop to trigger grid spawns
# via the Gaijinn API instead of direct CLI calls.
# GATEWAY_ENABLED=false
# GATEWAY_PORT=7377

# Enable cron integration for unattended sprint execution.
# When enabled, the autonomous pipeline runs compile-prompt -> scan -> analyze
# -> plan -> run-grid -> grid-spawn -> collect -> validate -> merge on a timer.
# CRON_ENABLED=false

# Autonomy loop interval (seconds) — how often the development loop
# polls for pending work. Default: 120 (2 minutes).
# GAIJINN_AUTONOMY_INTERVAL_SEC=120

# Background daemon mode — run the autonomy loop as a background process.
# GAIJINN_AUTONOMY_DAEMON=false

# ==============================================================================
# LOGGING
# ==============================================================================
# LOG_LEVEL=info
# LOG_FORMAT=json

# ==============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ==============================================================================
#
# Symptom: `401 Unauthorized` or `Auth failed`
#  Fix 1: Verify DEEPSEEK_API_KEY is set in ~/.hermes/.env
#  Fix 2: Run `hermes login` to re-authenticate (CLI-only method)
#  Fix 3: Check the key hasn't expired at https://platform.deepseek.com/api_keys
#  Fix 4: If using OAuth, verify DEEPSEEK_REFRESH_TOKEN + CLIENT_ID + SECRET
#
# Symptom: Grid workers use wrong model/provider
#  Fix: Set GRID_WORKER_MODEL and GRID_WORKER_PROVIDER explicitly above.
#       Also verify grid_executor in .gaijinn/project.json.
#
# Symptom: Orchestrator works but grid workers fail auth
#  Fix: Workers require DEEPSEEK_API_KEY in the env file. CLI login credentials
#       (from `hermes login`) are NOT inherited by worker spawns.
#
# Symptom: `hermes executable not found`
#  Fix: Install Hermes Agent per docs. Ensure PATH includes install dir.
#
# Symptom: Gateway port already in use
#  Fix: Change GATEWAY_PORT to a non-conflicting value (e.g., 7378).
#
# Symptom: Autonomy loop not firing
#  Fix: Verify GATEWAY_ENABLED=true and CRON_ENABLED=true.
#       Check GAIJINN_AUTONOMY_INTERVAL_SEC (min 60s).
#       Validate cron jobs in HERMES-DEVELOPMENT-ORDERS.md.
#
# Symptom: `gaijinn hermes` fails with wrong provider/model
#  Fix: Verify .gaijinn/project.json executor_profile matches env settings.
#       Or set: export GAIJINN_DEEPSEEK_PROVIDER=deepseek
